<h3>Step 1: Choose Your Space</h3>
{{#if rooms}}
  {{#unless room}}
  <p>Please choose the Space where you would like notifications sent:</p>
  {{else}}
  <p>We are sending notifications to your <strong>{{room.title}}</strong> Space. Change the Space where you would like notifications sent:</p>
  {{/unless}}
  <div class="list-group">
    {{#if room}}
    <a href="#" class="list-group-item active disabled">
      {{room.title}}
    </a>
    {{/if}}
    {{#each rooms}}
    <a href="/rooms/{{this.id}}" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">{{this.title}}</a>
    {{/each}}
  </div>
{{else}}
  No Spaces.
{{/if}}

<br/>
<hr/>
<br/>

{{#if integration_is_paypal}}
<h3>Step 2: Setup Your PayPal Integration</h3>
<p>To receive payment notifications in Cisco Spark you will need to setup your
  unique URL in your PayPal account. It's easy - follow these steps:</p>
<ol>
  <li>Log into your PayPal account.</li>
  <li>Follow the steps on <a href="http://www.paypal.com/ipn/" target="_blank">PayPal's website</a> to setup your IPN.</li>
  <li>Setup your IPN to use your unique URL (below).</li>
</ol>
<p>Here is your unique PayPal IPN URL:</p>
<input type="text" value="https://{{domain}}/api/inbound/paypal/ipn/{{user._id}}" class="form-control" disabled />
{{/if}}

{{#if integration_is_webhook}}
<h3>Step 2: Setup Your Webhook Integration</h3>
<p>To receive API alert notifications in Cisco Spark you will need to send
  requests to your unique URL. It's easy - send your request like this:</p>
<pre style="padding: 15px; background: #333; color: #fff;"><code>curl -X POST \
     -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
     -d '{"text":"Hello world!"}' \
     https://{{domain}}/api/inbound/webhook/{{user._id}}</pre></code>
<p>Here is your unique webhook URL:</p>
<input type="text" value="https://{{domain}}/api/inbound/webhook/{{user._id}}" class="form-control" disabled />
{{/if}}

{{#if integration_is_simplifycommerce}}
<h3>Step 2: Setup Your PayPal Integration</h3>
<p>To receive webhook notifications in Cisco Spark you will need to setup your
  unique URL in your Simplify account. It's easy - follow these steps:</p>
<ol>
  <li>Log into your Simplify Commerce account.</li>
  <li>Click your name in the top right and choose "Web Hooks".</li>
  <li>Enter your unique URL (below).</li>
  <li>Choose whether you want to send Sandbox or Production webhooks and hit "Save".</li>
</ol>
<p>Here is your unique Simplify Commerce Webhook URL:</p>
<input type="text" value="https://{{domain}}/api/inbound/simplifycommerce/{{user._id}}" class="form-control" disabled />
{{/if}}

